---
description: Source of truth index for project AI rules and workflows
globs:
  - "**/*"
alwaysApply: true
---

Binding rules: **`.ai-rules/`** — read before making changes. Do not duplicate rule bodies here.

Workflow guide: **`docs/development/ai/workflows.md`**

Start tasks with `.ai-rules/agent-orchestration.md` and `.ai-rules/context-map.md`.
Always apply `.ai-rules/anti-overengineering.md` through those indexes.

Builder / Reviewer workflow: `.ai-rules/agent-orchestration.md` §8 and `docs/development/ai/workflows.md`.
Cross-provider review: `scripts/ai/invoke-cross-reviewer.sh` when CLI is available.
Fallback: `.claude/agents/code-reviewer.md` (Claude), native CLI review (Codex), or `.commands/builder-handoff.md` (Cursor).

Optional (review / prompts, not binding):

- `agents/**/*.md`
- `.commands/**/*.md`
- `docs/specs/**/*.md`

Entry indexes: `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`.

Validation: `make validate` — commands in `.ai-rules/validation.md`.

OnTrack: `.cursor/rules/ontrack.mdc` (migration guardrails), `docs/archive/completed-migrations/backend-migration/`.
